249 static void MmwDemo_dssChirpIntHandler(uintptr_t arg)
250 {
251  MmwDemo_DSS_DataPathObj * dpObj = &gMmwDssMCB.dataPathObj[gMmwDssMCB.subFrameIndx];
252 
253  if((gMmwDssMCB.state == MmwDemo_DSS_STATE_STOPPED) ||
254  (gMmwDssMCB.dataPathContext.interFrameProcToken <= 0))
255  {
256  gMmwDssMCB.stats.chirpIntSkipCounter++;
257  return;
258  }
259 
260 #ifdef DBG
261  if (dpObj->chirpCount < NUM_CHIRP_TIME_STAMPS)
262  {
263  gChirpTimeStamp[dpObj->chirpCount] =
264  Cycleprofiler_getTimeStamp();
265  }
266 #endif
267 
268  if (dpObj->chirpCount == 0)
269  {
270  MmwDemo_DSS_DataPathObj * dpObjPrev = dpObj;
271  uint8_t subFrameIndxPrev;
272  if (gMmwDssMCB.numSubFrames > 1)
273  {
274  if (gMmwDssMCB.subFrameIndx == 0)
275  {
276  subFrameIndxPrev = gMmwDssMCB.numSubFrames - 1;
277  }
278  else
279  {
280  subFrameIndxPrev = gMmwDssMCB.subFrameIndx - 1;
281  }
282  dpObjPrev = &gMmwDssMCB.dataPathObj[subFrameIndxPrev];
283  }
284 
285  /* Note: this is valid after the first frame */
286  dpObjPrev->timingInfo.interFrameProcessingEndMargin =
287  Cycleprofiler_getTimeStamp() - dpObjPrev->timingInfo.interFrameProcessingEndTime -
288  dpObjPrev->timingInfo.subFrameSwitchingCycles;
289  }
290  else if (dpObj->chirpCount == dpObj->numChirpsPerChirpEvent)
291  {
292  dpObj->timingInfo.chirpProcessingEndMarginMin =
293  Cycleprofiler_getTimeStamp() - dpObj->timingInfo.chirpProcessingEndTime;
294  dpObj->timingInfo.chirpProcessingEndMarginMax =
295  dpObj->timingInfo.chirpProcessingEndMarginMin;
296  }
297  else
298  {
299  uint32_t margin = Cycleprofiler_getTimeStamp() - dpObj->timingInfo.chirpProcessingEndTime;
300  if (margin > dpObj->timingInfo.chirpProcessingEndMarginMax)
301  {
302  dpObj->timingInfo.chirpProcessingEndMarginMax = margin;
303  }
304  if (margin < dpObj->timingInfo.chirpProcessingEndMarginMin)
305  {
306  dpObj->timingInfo.chirpProcessingEndMarginMin = margin;
307  }
308  }
309  /* Increment interrupt counter for debugging purpose */
310  gMmwDssMCB.stats.chirpIntCounter++;
311 
312  /* Check if previous chirp processing has completed */
313  if (gMmwDssMCB.dataPathContext.chirpProcToken != 0)
314  {
315  MmwDemo_triggerDss2MssISR(MMWDEMO_DSS2MSS_CHIRP_PROC_DEADLINE_MISS_EXCEPTION);
316  DebugP_assert(0);
317  }
318 
319  gMmwDssMCB.dataPathContext.chirpProcToken++;
320 
321  /* Post event to notify chirp available interrupt */
322  Event_post(gMmwDssMCB.eventHandle, MMWDEMO_CHIRP_EVT);
323 }

378 static int32_t MmwDemo_dssMmwaveEventCallbackFxn(uint16_t msgId, uint16_t sbId, uint16_t sbLen, uint8_t *payload)
379 {
380  uint16_t asyncSB = RL_GET_SBID_FROM_UNIQ_SBID(sbId);
381 
382  /* Debug Message: */
383  /*System_printf ("Debug: MMWDemoDSS received BSS Event MsgId: %d [Sub Block Id: %d Sub Block Length: %d]\n",
384  msgId, sbId, sbLen); */
385 
386  /* Process the received message: */
387  switch (msgId)
388  {
389  case RL_RF_ASYNC_EVENT_MSG:
390  {
391  /* Received Asychronous Message: */
392  switch (asyncSB)
393  {
394  case RL_RF_AE_CPUFAULT_SB:
395  {
396  /* BSS fault */
397  MmwDemo_dssAssert(0);
398  break;
399  }
400  case RL_RF_AE_ESMFAULT_SB:
401  {
402  /* BSS fault */
403  MmwDemo_dssAssert(0);
404  break;
405  }
406  case RL_RF_AE_ANALOG_FAULT_SB:
407  {
408  /* Analog Fault */
409  MmwDemo_dssAssert(0);
410  break;
411  }
412  case RL_RF_AE_INITCALIBSTATUS_SB:
413  {
414  /* This event should be handled by mmwave internally, ignore the event here */
415  break;
416  }
417 
418  case RL_RF_AE_FRAME_TRIGGER_RDY_SB:
419  {
420  /* Post event to datapath task notify BSS events */
421  Event_post(gMmwDssMCB.eventHandle, MMWDEMO_BSS_FRAME_TRIGGER_READY_EVT);
422 
423  break;
424  }
425  case RL_RF_AE_MON_TIMING_FAIL_REPORT_SB:
426  {
427  /* Increment the statistics to reports that the calibration failed */
428  gMmwDssMCB.stats.numFailedTimingReports++;
429  break;
430  }
431  case RL_RF_AE_RUN_TIME_CALIB_REPORT_SB:
432  {
433  /* Increment the statistics to indicate that a calibration report was received */
434  gMmwDssMCB.stats.numCalibrationReports++;
435  break;
436  }
437  case RL_RF_AE_FRAME_END_SB:
438  {
439  gMmwDssMCB.stats.bssStopAsyncEvt++;
440  /*Received Frame Stop async event from BSS. Post event to datapath task.*/
441  Event_post(gMmwDssMCB.eventHandle, MMWDEMO_BSS_STOP_COMPLETE_EVT);
442  break;
443  }
444  default:
445  {
446  System_printf ("Error: Asynchronous Event SB Id %d not handled\n", asyncSB);
447  break;
448  }
449  }
450  break;
451  }
452  default:
453  {
454  System_printf ("Error: Asynchronous message %d is NOT handled\n", msgId);
455  break;
456  }
457  }
458  return 0;
459 }

583 {

586  {

596  /* Apply configuration to specific subframe (or to position zero for the legacy case

647 static void MmwDemo_mboxReadTask(UArg arg0, UArg arg1)
648 {
649  MmwDemo_message message;
650  int32_t retVal = 0;
651  int8_t subFrameNum;
652  uint32_t log2NumAvgChirpsTemp;
653 
654  /* wait for new message and process all the messsages received from the peer */
655  while(1)
656  {
657  Semaphore_pend(gMmwDssMCB.mboxSemHandle, BIOS_WAIT_FOREVER);
658 
659  /* Read the message from the peer mailbox: We are not trying to protect the read
660  * from the peer mailbox because this is only being invoked from a single thread */
661  retVal = Mailbox_read(gMmwDssMCB.peerMailbox, (uint8_t*)&message, sizeof(MmwDemo_message));
662  if (retVal < 0)
663  {
664  /* Error: Unable to read the message. Setup the error code and return values */
665  System_printf ("Error: Mailbox read failed [Error code %d]\n", retVal);
666  }
667  else if (retVal == 0)
668  {
669  /* We are done: There are no messages available from the peer execution domain. */
670  continue;
671  }
672  else
673  {
674  /* Flush out the contents of the mailbox to indicate that we are done with the message. This will
675  * allow us to receive another message in the mailbox while we process the received message. */
676  Mailbox_readFlush (gMmwDssMCB.peerMailbox);
677 
678  /* Process the received message: */
679  subFrameNum = message.subFrameNum;
680 
681  switch (message.type)
682  {
683  case MMWDEMO_MSS2DSS_GUIMON_CFG:
684  {
685  /* Save guimon configuration */
686  MmwDemo_cfgUpdate((void *)&message.body.guiMonSel,
687  offsetof(MmwDemo_CliCfg_t, guiMonSel),
688  sizeof(MmwDemo_GuiMonSel), subFrameNum);
689  break;
690  }
691  case MMWDEMO_MSS2DSS_CFAR_RANGE_CFG:
692  {
693  MmwDemo_cfgUpdate((void *)&message.body.cfarCfg,
694  offsetof(MmwDemo_CliCfg_t, cfarCfgRange),
695  sizeof(MmwDemo_CfarCfg), subFrameNum);
696  break;
697  }
698  case MMWDEMO_MSS2DSS_CFAR_DOPPLER_CFG:
699  {
700  /* Save cfarDoppler configuration */
701  MmwDemo_cfgUpdate((void *)&message.body.cfarCfg,
702  offsetof(MmwDemo_CliCfg_t, cfarCfgDoppler),
703  sizeof(MmwDemo_CfarCfg), subFrameNum);
704 
705  break;
706  }
707  case MMWDEMO_MSS2DSS_PEAK_GROUPING_CFG:
708  {
709  /* Save Peak grouping configuration */
710  MmwDemo_cfgUpdate((void *)&message.body.peakGroupingCfg,
711  offsetof(MmwDemo_CliCfg_t, peakGroupingCfg),
712  sizeof(MmwDemo_PeakGroupingCfg), subFrameNum);
713  break;
714  }
715  case MMWDEMO_MSS2DSS_MULTI_OBJ_BEAM_FORM:
716  {
717  /* Save multi object beam forming configuration */
718  MmwDemo_cfgUpdate((void*)&message.body.multiObjBeamFormingCfg,
719  offsetof(MmwDemo_CliCfg_t, multiObjBeamFormingCfg),
720  sizeof(MmwDemo_MultiObjBeamFormingCfg),
721  subFrameNum);
722  break;
723  }
724  case MMWDEMO_MSS2DSS_CALIB_DC_RANGE_SIG:
725  {
726  /* Save of DC range antenna signature configuration */
727  MmwDemo_cfgUpdate((void *)&message.body.calibDcRangeSigCfg,
728  offsetof(MmwDemo_CliCfg_t, calibDcRangeSigCfg),
729  sizeof(MmwDemo_CalibDcRangeSigCfg), subFrameNum);
730 
731  log2NumAvgChirpsTemp = MmwDemo_floorLog2(message.body.calibDcRangeSigCfg.numAvgChirps);
732  /* Save log2NumAvgChirps */
733  if (subFrameNum == MMWDEMO_SUBFRAME_NUM_FRAME_LEVEL_CONFIG)
734  {
735  uint8_t indx;

873  }

876 
877  gMmwDssMCB.dataPathContext.interFrameProcToken--;
878 
879  gMmwDssMCB.loggingBufferAvailable = 1;
880

883  {

887  }

889  {

891  break;
892  }
893  default:
894  {
895  /* Message not support */
896  System_printf ("Error: unsupport Mailbox message id=%d\n", message.type);

899  }

946 int32_t MmwDemo_dssSendProcessOutputToMSS
947 (
948  uint8_t *ptrHsmBuffer,

951 )
952 {
953  uint32_t i;
954  uint8_t *ptrCurrBuffer;
955  uint32_t totalHsmSize = 0;
956  uint32_t totalPacketLen = sizeof(MmwDemo_output_message_header);
957  uint32_t itemPayloadLen;
958  int32_t retVal = 0;
959  MmwDemo_message message;
960  MmwDemo_GuiMonSel *pGuiMonSel;
961  uint32_t tlvIdx = 0;
962 
963  /* Get Gui Monitor configuration */
964  pGuiMonSel = &obj->cliCfg->guiMonSel;
965 
966  /* Validate input params */
967  if(ptrHsmBuffer == NULL)
968  {
969  retVal = -1;
970  goto Exit;
971  }
972 
973 
974  /* Clear message to MSS */
975  memset((void *)&message, 0, sizeof(MmwDemo_message));
976  message.type = MMWDEMO_DSS2MSS_DETOBJ_READY;
977  /* Header: */
978  message.body.detObj.header.platform = 0xA1642;
979  message.body.detObj.header.magicWord[0] = 0x0102;
980  message.body.detObj.header.magicWord[1] = 0x0304;
981  message.body.detObj.header.magicWord[2] = 0x0506;
982  message.body.detObj.header.magicWord[3] = 0x0708;

984  message.body.detObj.header.version = MMWAVE_SDK_VERSION_BUILD | //DEBUG_VERSION
985  (MMWAVE_SDK_VERSION_BUGFIX << 8) |
986  (MMWAVE_SDK_VERSION_MINOR << 16) |
987  (MMWAVE_SDK_VERSION_MAJOR << 24);
988 
989  /* Set pointer to HSM buffer */
990  ptrCurrBuffer = ptrHsmBuffer;
991 
992  /* Put detected Objects in HSM buffer: sizeof(MmwDemo_objOut_t) * numDetObj */
993  if ((pGuiMonSel->detectedObjects == 1) && (obj->numDetObj > 0))
994  {
995  /* Add objects descriptor */

997  descr.numDetetedObj = obj->numDetObj;
998  descr.xyzQFormat = obj->xyzOutputQFormat;
999  itemPayloadLen = sizeof(MmwDemo_output_message_dataObjDescr);
1000  totalHsmSize += itemPayloadLen;
1001  if(totalHsmSize > outputBufSize)
1002  {
1003  retVal = -1;
1004  goto Exit;
1005  }
1006  memcpy(ptrCurrBuffer, (void *)&descr, itemPayloadLen);
1007 
1008  /* Add array of objects */
1009  itemPayloadLen = sizeof(MmwDemo_detectedObj) * obj->numDetObj;
1010  totalHsmSize += itemPayloadLen;
1011  if(totalHsmSize > outputBufSize)
1012  {
1013  retVal = -1;
1014  goto Exit;
1015  }
1016  memcpy(&ptrCurrBuffer[sizeof(MmwDemo_output_message_dataObjDescr)], (void *)obj->detObj2D, itemPayloadLen);
1017 
1018  message.body.detObj.tlv[tlvIdx].length = itemPayloadLen + sizeof(MmwDemo_output_message_dataObjDescr);
1019  message.body.detObj.tlv[tlvIdx].type = MMWDEMO_OUTPUT_MSG_DETECTED_POINTS;
1020  message.body.detObj.tlv[tlvIdx].address = (uint32_t) ptrCurrBuffer;
1021  tlvIdx++;
1022 
1023  /* Incrementing pointer to HSM buffer */
1024  ptrCurrBuffer += itemPayloadLen + sizeof(MmwDemo_output_message_dataObjDescr);
1025  totalPacketLen += sizeof(MmwDemo_output_message_tl) + itemPayloadLen + sizeof(MmwDemo_output_message_dataObjDescr);
1026  }
1027 
1028  /* Sending range profile: 2bytes * numRangeBins */
1029  if (pGuiMonSel->logMagRange == 1)
1030  {
1031  itemPayloadLen = sizeof(uint16_t) * obj->numRangeBins;
1032  totalHsmSize += itemPayloadLen;
1033  if(totalHsmSize > outputBufSize)
1034  {
1035  retVal = -1;
1036  goto Exit;
1037  }
1038 
1039  uint16_t *ptrMatrix = (uint16_t *)ptrCurrBuffer;
1040  for(i = 0; i < obj->numRangeBins; i++)
1041  {
1042  ptrMatrix[i] = obj->detMatrix[i*obj->numDopplerBins];
1043  }
1044 
1045  message.body.detObj.tlv[tlvIdx].length = itemPayloadLen;
1046  message.body.detObj.tlv[tlvIdx].type = MMWDEMO_OUTPUT_MSG_RANGE_PROFILE;
1047  message.body.detObj.tlv[tlvIdx].address = (uint32_t) ptrCurrBuffer;
1048  tlvIdx++;
1049 
1050  /* Incrementing pointer to HSM buffer */
1051  ptrCurrBuffer = (uint8_t *)((uint32_t)ptrHsmBuffer + totalHsmSize);
1052  totalPacketLen += sizeof(MmwDemo_output_message_tl) + itemPayloadLen;
1053  }
1054 
1055  /* Sending range profile: 2bytes * numRangeBins */
1056  if (pGuiMonSel->noiseProfile == 1)
1057  {
1058  uint32_t maxDopIdx = obj->numDopplerBins/2 -1;
1059  itemPayloadLen = sizeof(uint16_t) * obj->numRangeBins;
1060  totalHsmSize += itemPayloadLen;
1061  if(totalHsmSize > outputBufSize)
1062  {
1063  retVal = -1;
1064  goto Exit;
1065  }
1066 
1067  uint16_t *ptrMatrix = (uint16_t *)ptrCurrBuffer;
1068  for(i = 0; i < obj->numRangeBins; i++)
1069  {
1070  ptrMatrix[i] = obj->detMatrix[i*obj->numDopplerBins + maxDopIdx];
1071  }
1072 
1073  message.body.detObj.tlv[tlvIdx].length = itemPayloadLen;
1074  message.body.detObj.tlv[tlvIdx].type = MMWDEMO_OUTPUT_MSG_NOISE_PROFILE;
1075  message.body.detObj.tlv[tlvIdx].address = (uint32_t) ptrCurrBuffer;
1076  tlvIdx++;
1077 
1078  /* Incrementing pointer to HSM buffer */
1079  ptrCurrBuffer = (uint8_t *)((uint32_t)ptrHsmBuffer + totalHsmSize);
1080  totalPacketLen += sizeof(MmwDemo_output_message_tl) + itemPayloadLen;
1081  }
1082 
1083  /* Sending range Azimuth Heat Map */
1084  if (pGuiMonSel->rangeAzimuthHeatMap == 1)
1085  {
1086  itemPayloadLen = obj->numRangeBins * obj->numVirtualAntAzim * sizeof(cmplx16ImRe_t);
1087  message.body.detObj.tlv[tlvIdx].length = itemPayloadLen;
1088  message.body.detObj.tlv[tlvIdx].type = MMWDEMO_OUTPUT_MSG_AZIMUT_STATIC_HEAT_MAP;
1089  message.body.detObj.tlv[tlvIdx].address = (uint32_t) obj->azimuthStaticHeatMap;
1090  tlvIdx++;
1091 
1092  totalPacketLen += sizeof(MmwDemo_output_message_tl) + itemPayloadLen;
1093  }
1094 
1095 
1096  /* Sending range Doppler Heat Map */
1097  if (pGuiMonSel->rangeDopplerHeatMap == 1)
1098  {
1099  itemPayloadLen = obj->numRangeBins * obj->numDopplerBins * sizeof(uint16_t);
1100  message.body.detObj.tlv[tlvIdx].length = itemPayloadLen;
1101  message.body.detObj.tlv[tlvIdx].type = MMWDEMO_OUTPUT_MSG_RANGE_DOPPLER_HEAT_MAP;
1102  message.body.detObj.tlv[tlvIdx].address = (uint32_t) obj->detMatrix;
1103  tlvIdx++;
1104 
1105  totalPacketLen += sizeof(MmwDemo_output_message_tl) + itemPayloadLen;
1106  }
1107 
1108  /* Sending stats information */
1109  if (pGuiMonSel->statsInfo == 1)
1110  {
1111  MmwDemo_output_message_stats stats;
1112  itemPayloadLen = sizeof(MmwDemo_output_message_stats);
1113  totalHsmSize += itemPayloadLen;
1114  if(totalHsmSize > outputBufSize)
1115  {
1116  retVal = -1;
1117  goto Exit;
1118  }
1119 
1120  stats.interChirpProcessingMargin = (uint32_t) (obj->timingInfo.chirpProcessingEndMarginMin/DSP_CLOCK_MHZ);
1121  stats.interFrameProcessingMargin = (uint32_t) (obj->timingInfo.interFrameProcessingEndMargin/DSP_CLOCK_MHZ);
1122  stats.interFrameProcessingTime = (uint32_t) (obj->timingInfo.interFrameProcCycles/DSP_CLOCK_MHZ);
1123  stats.transmitOutputTime = (uint32_t) (obj->timingInfo.transmitOutputCycles/DSP_CLOCK_MHZ);
1124  stats.activeFrameCPULoad = obj->timingInfo.activeFrameCPULoad;
1125  stats.interFrameCPULoad = obj->timingInfo.interFrameCPULoad;
1126  memcpy(ptrCurrBuffer, (void *)&stats, itemPayloadLen);
1127 
1128  message.body.detObj.tlv[tlvIdx].length = itemPayloadLen;
1129  message.body.detObj.tlv[tlvIdx].type = MMWDEMO_OUTPUT_MSG_STATS;
1130  message.body.detObj.tlv[tlvIdx].address = (uint32_t) ptrCurrBuffer;;
1131  tlvIdx++;
1132 
1133  /* Incrementing pointer to HSM buffer */
1134  ptrCurrBuffer = (uint8_t *)((uint32_t)ptrHsmBuffer + totalHsmSize);
1135  totalPacketLen += sizeof(MmwDemo_output_message_tl) + itemPayloadLen;
1136  }
1137 
1138  if( retVal == 0)
1139  {
1140  message.body.detObj.header.numTLVs = tlvIdx;
1141  /* Round up packet length to multiple of MMWDEMO_OUTPUT_MSG_SEGMENT_LEN */
1142  message.body.detObj.header.totalPacketLen = MMWDEMO_OUTPUT_MSG_SEGMENT_LEN *
1143  ((totalPacketLen + (MMWDEMO_OUTPUT_MSG_SEGMENT_LEN-1))/MMWDEMO_OUTPUT_MSG_SEGMENT_LEN);
1144  message.body.detObj.header.timeCpuCycles = Cycleprofiler_getTimeStamp();
1145  message.body.detObj.header.frameNumber = gMmwDssMCB.stats.frameStartIntCounter;
1146  message.body.detObj.header.subFrameNumber = gMmwDssMCB.subFrameIndx;
1147  if (MmwDemo_mboxWrite(&message) != 0)
1148  {
1149  retVal = -1;
1150  }
1151  }
1152 Exit:
1153  return retVal;
1154 }

1185 void MmwDemo_dssDataPathOutputLogging(MmwDemo_DSS_DataPathObj * dataPathObj)
1186 {

1188 
1189  /* Sending detected objects to logging buffer and shipped out from MSS UART */
1190  if (gMmwDssMCB.loggingBufferAvailable == 1)
1191  {
1192  /* Set the logging buffer available flag to be 0 */
1193  gMmwDssMCB.loggingBufferAvailable = 0;
1194

1196  if(dataPathObj->cliCfg->lvdsStreamCfg.isSwEnabled != 0)

1199  reconfigured every frame/subframe because number of detected objects
1200  may change every frame/subframe which implies that the size of
1201  the streamed data may change. */
1202  if(gMmwDssMCB.lvdsStream.swSessionHandle != NULL)
1203  {
1204  MmwDemo_LVDSStreamDeleteSwSession(gMmwDssMCB.lvdsStream.swSessionHandle);

1207  if (MmwDemo_LVDSStreamSwConfig(dataPathObj) < 0)

1210  return;
1211  }

1213  gMmwDssMCB.lvdsStream.userDataHeader.frameNum = gMmwDssMCB.stats.frameStartEvt;
1214  gMmwDssMCB.lvdsStream.userDataHeader.detObjNum = dataPathObj->numDetObj;
1215  gMmwDssMCB.lvdsStream.userDataHeader.reserved = 0xABCD;
1216

1218  start to stream over LVDS.*/
1219  if(CBUFF_activateSession (gMmwDssMCB.lvdsStream.swSessionHandle, &errCode) < 0)
1220  {
1221  System_printf("Failed to activate CBUFF session for LVDS stream SW. errCode=%d\n",errCode);
1222  return;
1223  }
1224  }
1225 
1226  /* Save output in logging buffer - HSRAM memory and a message is sent to MSS to notify
1227  logging buffer is ready */

1229  (uint32_t)MMW_DATAPATH_DET_PAYLOAD_SIZE,
1230  dataPathObj) < 0)
1231  {
1232  /* Increment logging error */
1233  gMmwDssMCB.stats.detObjLoggingErr++;
1234  }
1235 
1236  }
1237  else
1238  {
1239  /* Logging buffer is not available, skip saving detected objects to logging buffer */
1240  gMmwDssMCB.stats.detObjLoggingSkip++;
1241  }

1740 bool MmwDemo_parseProfileAndChirpConfig(MmwDemo_DSS_DataPathObj *dataPathObj,
1741  MMWave_CtrlCfg* ptrCtrlCfg, uint8_t subFrameIndx)
1742 {
1743  uint16_t frameChirpStartIdx;
1744  uint16_t frameChirpEndIdx;
1745  uint16_t numLoops;
1746  int16_t frameTotalChirps;
1747  int32_t errCode;
1748  uint32_t profileLoopIdx, chirpLoopIdx;
1749  bool foundValidProfile = false;
1750  uint16_t channelTxEn;
1751  uint8_t channel;
1752  uint8_t numRxChannels = 0;
1753  MMWave_OpenCfg* ptrOpenCfg;
1754  uint8_t rxAntOrder [SYS_COMMON_NUM_RX_CHANNEL];
1755  uint8_t txAntOrder [SYS_COMMON_NUM_TX_ANTENNAS];
1756  int32_t i;
1757  int32_t txIdx, rxIdx;
1758 
1759  /* Get data path object and control configuration */
1760  ptrOpenCfg = &gMmwDssMCB.cfg.openCfg;
1761 
1762  /* Get the Transmit channel enable mask: */
1763  channelTxEn = ptrOpenCfg->chCfg.txChannelEn;
1764 
1765  /* Find total number of Rx Channels */
1766  for (channel = 0; channel < SYS_COMMON_NUM_RX_CHANNEL; channel++)
1767  {
1768  rxAntOrder[channel] = 0;
1769  if(ptrOpenCfg->chCfg.rxChannelEn & (0x1U << channel))
1770  {
1771  rxAntOrder[numRxChannels] = channel;
1772  /* Track the number of receive channels: */
1773  numRxChannels += 1;
1774  }
1775  }
1776  dataPathObj->numRxAntennas = numRxChannels;
1777 
1778  if (ptrCtrlCfg->dfeDataOutputMode == MMWave_DFEDataOutputMode_ADVANCED_FRAME)
1779  {
1780  MmwDemo_dssAssert(
1781  ptrCtrlCfg->u.advancedFrameCfg.frameCfg.frameSeq.subFrameCfg[subFrameIndx].numOfBurst == 1);
1782  }
1783 
1784  /* read frameCfg chirp start/stop*/
1785  frameChirpStartIdx = MmwDemo_getChirpStartIdx(ptrCtrlCfg, subFrameIndx);
1786  frameChirpEndIdx = MmwDemo_getChirpEndIdx(ptrCtrlCfg, subFrameIndx);
1787  numLoops = MmwDemo_getNumLoops(ptrCtrlCfg, subFrameIndx);
1788 
1789  frameTotalChirps = frameChirpEndIdx - frameChirpStartIdx + 1;
1790 
1791  /* since validChirpTxEnBits is static array of 32 */
1792  MmwDemo_dssAssert(frameTotalChirps <= 32);
1793 
1794  /* loop for profiles and find if it has valid chirps */
1795  /* we support only one profile in this processing chain */
1796  for (profileLoopIdx = 0;
1797  ((profileLoopIdx < MMWAVE_MAX_PROFILE) && (foundValidProfile == false));
1798  profileLoopIdx++)
1799  {
1800  uint32_t mmWaveNumChirps = 0;
1801  bool validProfileHasOneTxPerChirp = false;
1802  bool validChirpHasOneTxPerChirp = false;
1803  uint16_t validProfileTxEn = 0;
1804  uint16_t validChirpTxEnBits[32] = {0};
1805  MMWave_ProfileHandle profileHandle;
1806 
1807  profileHandle = MmwDemo_getProfileHandle(ptrCtrlCfg, profileLoopIdx);
1808  if (profileHandle == NULL)
1809  continue; /* skip this profile */
1810 
1811  /* get numChirps for this profile; skip error checking */
1812  MMWave_getNumChirps(profileHandle, &mmWaveNumChirps, &errCode);
1813  /* loop for chirps and find if it has valid chirps for the frame
1814  looping around for all chirps in a profile, in case
1815  there are duplicate chirps
1816  */
1817  for (chirpLoopIdx = 1; chirpLoopIdx <= mmWaveNumChirps; chirpLoopIdx++)
1818  {
1819  MMWave_ChirpHandle chirpHandle;
1820  /* get handle and read ChirpCfg */
1821  if (MMWave_getChirpHandle(profileHandle, chirpLoopIdx, &chirpHandle, &errCode)==0)
1822  {
1823  rlChirpCfg_t chirpCfg;
1824  if (MMWave_getChirpCfg(chirpHandle, &chirpCfg, &errCode)==0)
1825  {
1826  uint16_t chirpTxEn = chirpCfg.txEnable;
1827  /* do chirps fall in range and has valid antenna enabled */
1828  if ((chirpCfg.chirpStartIdx >= frameChirpStartIdx) &&
1829  (chirpCfg.chirpEndIdx <= frameChirpEndIdx) &&
1830  ((chirpTxEn & channelTxEn) > 0))
1831  {
1832  uint16_t idx = 0;
1833  for (idx = (chirpCfg.chirpStartIdx - frameChirpStartIdx);
1834  idx <= (chirpCfg.chirpEndIdx - frameChirpStartIdx); idx++)
1835  {
1836  validChirpTxEnBits[idx] = chirpTxEn;
1837  foundValidProfile = true;
1838  }
1839 
1840  }
1841  }
1842  }
1843  }
1844  /* now loop through unique chirps and check if we found all of the ones
1845  needed for the frame and then determine the azimuth antenna
1846  configuration
1847  */
1848  if (foundValidProfile) {
1849  for (chirpLoopIdx = 0; chirpLoopIdx < frameTotalChirps; chirpLoopIdx++)
1850  {
1851  uint16_t chirpTxEn = validChirpTxEnBits[chirpLoopIdx];
1852  validChirpHasOneTxPerChirp = false;
1853  if (chirpTxEn == 0) {
1854  /* this profile doesnt have all the needed chirps */
1855  foundValidProfile = false;
1856  break;
1857  }
1858 
1859  if(dataPathObj->cliCfg->bpmCfg.isEnabled)
1860  {
1861  /*For configuration purposes, BPM should be treated as if it was TDM with 2 TX antennas
1862  and one TX per chirp. This way, all logic below will follow through for BPM.
1863  Just need to check here if all TX antennas are enabled for BPM.*/
1864  validChirpHasOneTxPerChirp = true;
1865  /* In case of BPM check if both TX antennas are enabled*/
1866  if(chirpTxEn != 0x3)
1867  {
1868  /* This frame is configured as BPM but this chirp does not enable both TX antennas*/
1869  foundValidProfile = false;
1870  System_printf("Bad BPM configuration. chirpTxEn=%d for chirp %d \n",chirpTxEn,chirpLoopIdx);
1871  break;
1872  }
1873  }
1874  else
1875  {
1876  validChirpHasOneTxPerChirp = ((chirpTxEn == 0x1) || (chirpTxEn == 0x2));
1877  }
1878  /* if this is the first chirp, record the chirp's
1879  MIMO config as profile's MIMO config. We dont handle intermix
1880  at this point */
1881  if (chirpLoopIdx==0) {
1882  validProfileHasOneTxPerChirp = validChirpHasOneTxPerChirp;
1883  }
1884  /* check the chirp's MIMO config against Profile's MIMO config */
1885  if (validChirpHasOneTxPerChirp != validProfileHasOneTxPerChirp)
1886  {
1887  /* this profile doesnt have all chirps with same MIMO config */
1888  foundValidProfile = false;
1889  break;
1890  }
1891  /* save the antennas actually enabled in this profile */
1892  validProfileTxEn |= chirpTxEn;
1893  }
1894  }
1895 
1896  /* found valid chirps for the frame; mark this profile valid */
1897  if (foundValidProfile == true) {
1898  rlProfileCfg_t profileCfg;
1899  uint32_t numTxAntAzim = 0;
1900  uint32_t numTxAntElev = 0;
1901  rlProfileCfg_t ptrProfileCfg;
1902 
1903  /* Get profile id from profile config */
1904  if(MMWave_getProfileCfg(profileHandle, &ptrProfileCfg, &errCode) < 0)
1905  {
1906  MmwDemo_dssAssert(0);
1907  }
1908  dataPathObj->validProfileIdx = ptrProfileCfg.profileId;
1909 
1910  dataPathObj->numTxAntennas = 0;
1911  if (!validProfileHasOneTxPerChirp)
1912  {
1913  numTxAntAzim=1;
1914  }
1915  else
1916  {
1917  if (validProfileTxEn & 0x1)
1918  {
1919  numTxAntAzim++;
1920  }
1921  if (validProfileTxEn & 0x2)
1922  {
1923  numTxAntAzim++;
1924  }
1925  }

1929  dataPathObj->numVirtualAntElev = numTxAntElev * dataPathObj->numRxAntennas;
1930  dataPathObj->numVirtualAntennas = dataPathObj->numVirtualAntAzim + dataPathObj->numVirtualAntElev;
1931 
1932  /* Sanity Check: Ensure that the number of antennas is within system limits */
1933  MmwDemo_dssAssert (dataPathObj->numVirtualAntennas > 0);
1934  MmwDemo_dssAssert (dataPathObj->numVirtualAntennas <= (SYS_COMMON_NUM_TX_ANTENNAS * SYS_COMMON_NUM_RX_CHANNEL));
1935 
1936  /* Copy the Rx channel compensation coefficients from common area to data path structure */
1937  if (validProfileHasOneTxPerChirp)
1938  {
1939  for (i = 0; i < dataPathObj->numTxAntennas; i++)
1940  {
1941  if(dataPathObj->cliCfg->bpmCfg.isEnabled)
1942  {
1943  /*If BPM is enabled, need to assume order of the antennas as it can not
1944  be derived from the chirp/profile configuration because both TX antennas
1945  are enabled in both chirps. Will assume that the order is 0,1,...[numTxAntennas-1]*/
1946  txAntOrder[i] = i;
1947  }
1948  else
1949  {
1950  txAntOrder[i] = MmwDemo_floorLog2(validChirpTxEnBits[i]);
1951  }
1952  }
1953  for (txIdx = 0; txIdx < dataPathObj->numTxAntennas; txIdx++)
1954  {
1955  for (rxIdx = 0; rxIdx < dataPathObj->numRxAntennas; rxIdx++)

1957  dataPathObj->compRxChanCfg.rxChPhaseComp[txIdx*dataPathObj->numRxAntennas + rxIdx] =
1958  dataPathObj->cliCommonCfg->compRxChanCfg.rxChPhaseComp[txAntOrder[txIdx]*SYS_COMMON_NUM_RX_CHANNEL + rxAntOrder[rxIdx]];
1959 
1960  }
1961 
1962  }
1963  }
1964  else
1965  {
1966  cmplx16ImRe_t one;
1967  one.imag = 0;
1968  one.real = 0x7fff;
1969  for (txIdx = 0; txIdx < dataPathObj->numTxAntennas; txIdx++)
1970  {
1971  for (rxIdx = 0; rxIdx < dataPathObj->numRxAntennas; rxIdx++)
1972  {
1973  dataPathObj->compRxChanCfg.rxChPhaseComp[txIdx*dataPathObj->numRxAntennas + rxIdx] = one;
1974  }
1975 
1976  }
1977  }
1978  /* Get the profile configuration: */
1979  if (MMWave_getProfileCfg (profileHandle, &profileCfg, &errCode) < 0)
1980  {
1981  System_printf ("Error: Unable to get the profile configuration [Error code %d]\n", errCode);
1982  MmwDemo_dssAssert (0);
1983  return -1;
1984  }
1985 
1986  /* multiplicity of 4 due to windowing library function requirement */
1987  if ((profileCfg.numAdcSamples % 4) != 0)
1988  {
1989  System_printf("Number of ADC samples must be multiple of 4\n");
1990  MmwDemo_dssAssert(0);
1991  }
1992  dataPathObj->numAdcSamples = profileCfg.numAdcSamples;
1993  dataPathObj->numRangeBins = MmwDemo_pow2roundup(dataPathObj->numAdcSamples);
1994  dataPathObj->numChirpsPerFrame = (frameChirpEndIdx -frameChirpStartIdx + 1) *

1997  dataPathObj->numDopplerBins = dataPathObj->numChirpsPerFrame/dataPathObj->numTxAntennas;

2000  Minimum size of 16 due to DSPLib restriction - FFT size must be bigger than 16.*/
2001  if (((dataPathObj->numDopplerBins % 4) != 0) ||
2002  (dataPathObj->numDopplerBins < 16))
2003  {
2004  System_printf("Number of Doppler bins must be at least 16 and it must be a multiple of 4.\n");
2005  MmwDemo_dssAssert(0);
2006  }
2007

2009  dataPathObj->cliCfg->multiObjBeamFormingCfg.enabled)
2010  {
2011  System_printf("Simultaneous multi object beam forming and extended maximum velocity is not supported.\n");
2012  MmwDemo_dssAssert(0);
2013  }
2014 
2015  if (dataPathObj->cliCfg->extendedMaxVelocityCfg.enabled && numTxAntAzim == 1)
2016  {
2017  System_printf("Extended maximum velocity technique is supported only in TDM MIMO\n");
2018  MmwDemo_dssAssert(0);
2019  }
2020 
2021 #ifndef MMW_ENABLE_NEGATIVE_FREQ_SLOPE
2022  /* Check frequency slope */
2023  if (profileCfg.freqSlopeConst < 0)
2024  {
2025  System_printf("Frequency slope must be positive\n");
2026  MmwDemo_dssAssert(0);
2027  }
2028 #endif
2029  dataPathObj->rangeResolution = MMWDEMO_SPEED_OF_LIGHT_IN_METERS_PER_SEC *
2030  profileCfg.digOutSampleRate * 1e3 /
2031  (2 * profileCfg.freqSlopeConst * ((3.6*1e3*900) /
2032  (1U << 26)) * 1e12 * dataPathObj->numRangeBins);
2033  dataPathObj->xyzOutputQFormat = (uint8_t) ceil(log10(16. /
2034  fabs(dataPathObj->rangeResolution))/log10(2));
2035  }
2036  }
2037  return foundValidProfile;

2046 void MmwDemo_parseAdcBufCfg(MmwDemo_DSS_DataPathObj *dataPathObj)
2047 {
2048  uint8_t numBytePerSample = 0;
2049  uint32_t chirpThreshold;
2050  uint32_t maxChirpThreshold;
2051  uint32_t bytesPerChirp;
2052  MmwDemo_ADCBufCfg *adcBufCfg = &dataPathObj->cliCfg->adcBufCfg;
2053 
2054  /* Check if ADC configuration is supported:*/
2055  /* ADC out bits: must be 16 Bits */
2056  MmwDemo_dssAssert(dataPathObj->cfg->openCfg.adcOutCfg.fmt.b2AdcBits == 2);
2057 
2058  /* ADC data format: must be complex */
2059  /*adcCfg command*/
2060  if((dataPathObj->cfg->openCfg.adcOutCfg.fmt.b2AdcOutFmt != 1) &&
2061  (dataPathObj->cfg->openCfg.adcOutCfg.fmt.b2AdcOutFmt != 2))
2062  {
2063  MmwDemo_dssAssert(0);
2064  }
2065  /*adcbufCfg command*/
2066  MmwDemo_dssAssert(adcBufCfg->adcFmt == 0);
2067 
2068  /* ADC channel interleave mode: must be non-interleaved */
2069  MmwDemo_dssAssert(adcBufCfg->chInterleave == 1);
2070 
2071  /* Complex dataFormat has 4 bytes */
2072  numBytePerSample = 4;
2073 
2074  /* calculate max possible chirp threshold */
2075  bytesPerChirp = dataPathObj->numAdcSamples * dataPathObj->numRxAntennas * numBytePerSample;
2076 
2077  /* find maximum number of full chirps that can fit in the ADCBUF memory, while
2078  also being able to divide numChirpsPerFrame, we do not want remainder processing */
2079  maxChirpThreshold = SOC_XWR16XX_DSS_ADCBUF_SIZE / bytesPerChirp;
2080 
2081  /* There is a maximum of 8 CPs and CQs, so lets limit maxChirpThreshold to be that*/
2082  if(maxChirpThreshold > SYS_COMMON_CQ_MAX_CHIRP_THRESHOLD)
2083  {
2084  maxChirpThreshold = SYS_COMMON_CQ_MAX_CHIRP_THRESHOLD;
2085  }
2086 
2087  if (maxChirpThreshold >= dataPathObj->numChirpsPerFrame)
2088  {
2089  maxChirpThreshold = dataPathObj->numChirpsPerFrame;
2090  }
2091  else
2092  {
2093  /* find largest divisor of numChirpsPerFrame no bigger than maxChirpThreshold */
2094  while (dataPathObj->numChirpsPerFrame % maxChirpThreshold)
2095  {
2096  maxChirpThreshold--;
2097  }
2098  }
2099 
2100  /* ADCBuf control function requires argument alignment at 4 bytes boundary */
2101  chirpThreshold = adcBufCfg->chirpThreshold;
2102 
2103  /* if automatic, set to the calculated max */
2104  if (chirpThreshold == 0)
2105  {
2106  chirpThreshold = maxChirpThreshold;
2107  }
2108  else
2109  {
2110  if (chirpThreshold > maxChirpThreshold)
2111  {
2112  System_printf("Desired chirpThreshold %d higher than max possible of %d, setting to max\n",
2113  chirpThreshold, maxChirpThreshold);
2114  chirpThreshold = maxChirpThreshold;
2115  }
2116  else
2117  {
2118  /* check for divisibility of the user provided threshold */
2119  MmwDemo_dssAssert((dataPathObj->numChirpsPerFrame % chirpThreshold) == 0);
2120  }
2121  }
2122 
2123  /* Save info in data path Object */
2124  dataPathObj->numChirpsPerChirpEvent = chirpThreshold;
2125  dataPathObj->numBytePerSample = numBytePerSample;
2126 }

2740  if (gMmwDssMCB.ctrlHandle == NULL)

2742  /* Error: Unable to initialize the mmWave control module */

2744  return;

2749  * TEST: Synchronization
2750  * - The synchronization API always needs to be invoked.
2751  ******************************************************************************/

2753  {
2754  int32_t syncStatus;
2755 
2756  /* Get the synchronization status: */

2762  return;

2764  if (syncStatus == 1)
2765  {
2766  /* Synchronization acheived: */
2767  break;
2768  }
2769  /* Sleep and poll again: */
2770  Task_sleep(1);
2771  }
2772 
2773  /* Send the DSS to MSS signalling ISR payload address to the DSS. Note this
2774  should be done after both sides mailboxes have been opened, and because
2775  MMWave_sync above is a good one to check for synchronization, this is a good place */
2776  message.type = MMWDEMO_DSS2MSS_ISR_INFO_ADDRESS;

2785  Task_Params_init(&taskParams);

2787  taskParams.stackSize = 4*1024;

2792  *****************************************************************************/

2796  return;

2799  gMmwDssMCB.state = MmwDemo_DSS_STATE_INIT;
2800 
2801  /* Start data path task */
2802  Task_Params_init(&taskParams);

2804  taskParams.stackSize = 4*1024;
2805  Task_create(MmwDemo_dssDataPathTask, &taskParams, NULL);
